parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The abrupt downshifting of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lunge forward, potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The transmission shifts down abruptly to 1st gear
the vehicle lunges forward
the transmission shifts erratically
the vehicle is slow to shift into the next gear
high RPM before shifting
and the vehicle flares during shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to repair the power train recall can cause the transfer case to fail, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The transfer case needs to be replaced
the vehicle is not repaired despite the recall notification.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to repair the EGI harness recall can cause the transmission power wire to fail, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The transmission power wire continuity test fails
the technician does not find any evidence of visible damage on or near the transmission power wires OEM splice.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine/transmission power control can cause the vehicle to fail to accelerate, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to accelerate during a rolling stop
the vehicle rolls slowly into oncoming traffic
the vehicle shifts erratically
and the vehicle is slow to shift into the next gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the idle air controller can cause the engine to lose power, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The engine idles at high RPM
the engine loses power
the check engine light comes on
and the code reader indicates a fault in the idle air controller.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the dashboard to malfunction, leading to a loss of critical vehicle information, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The dashboard blinks out and resets while driving
especially when charging phones.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TCM can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to the vehicle becoming stranded or unable to move, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle leaves the driver stranded on the side of the road
the transmission thinks it's in park
and the vehicle needs to be towed to clear the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The high-pressure fuel pump and low-pressure fuel pump fail
causing the vehicle to lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the GPS navigation system can cause the driver to become disoriented, leading to a loss of control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The GPS navigation system map arrow goes backwards
even after replacing the GPS system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic braking system can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop or lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The automatic braking system applies itself on the highway
causing the truck to stop moving forward
and multiple warning signals appear in the truck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A vehicle fire can cause serious injuries or fatalities, as well as damage to the vehicle and surrounding property.
symptoms: A smoke odor is noticed while driving
followed by flames between the cabin and the rear of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hesitation on acceleration can lead to a safety risk, especially when immediate acceleration is needed, such as when merging onto a highway or avoiding a potential collision.
symptoms: Hesitation on acceleration from both still and moving normal highway speeds
rarely achieving steady
smooth
and immediate acceleration
delayed response to throttle input
feeling of lag or stuttering when pressing the accelerator pedal.
